revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{Uses TemplateStyles|Template:Ruby/styles.css}}
{{COinS safe|n}}
<!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE -->

This template should only be used for [[Japanese language|Japanese]] [[ruby character]]s.  Otherwise, please use the generic [[Template:ruby]] with the [[Template:lang]], or [[Template:ruby-zh-p]] or [[Template:ruby-zh-b]] for Chinese [[pinyin]] or [[bopomofo]] respectively.

== Usage ==
<code><nowiki>{{Ruby-ja | kanji | kana}}</nowiki></code>

ex. <code><nowiki>{{Ruby-ja|全|すべ}}て</nowiki></code> → {{Ruby-ja|全|すべ}}て

== TemplateData ==
{{TemplateData header}}
<templatedata>
{
	"description": "This template is used to add a furigana to facilitate easy understanding of Japanese characters",
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"label": "Kanji",
			"description": "The Kanji",
			"type": "string",
			"required": true,
			"suggested": true
		},
		"2": {
			"label": "Furigana",
			"description": "It is a Japanese reading aid, consisting of smaller Kana, or syllabic characters, printed next to a Kanji",
			"type": "string",
			"required": true,
			"suggested": true
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>

== See also ==
* {{tl|ruby}}
* {{tl|ruby line}}

